---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Container from "../../components/shared/Container.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Service Scope — Flores Nexus Group LLC"
  description="What is included and excluded in each Flores Nexus Group LLC plan. Small update definition, change request levels, domain policy, and add-ons."
  lang="en"
>
  <main class="pt-24 pb-20">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

        <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 italic mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          This document is provided for informational purposes. Flores Nexus Group LLC recommends consulting a licensed Florida attorney before relying on these terms for legal decisions.
        </p>

        <div class="mb-10">
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-heading-1 mb-2">Service Scope</h1>
          <p class="text-heading-3 text-sm mb-2">What is included and excluded in each plan</p>
          <p class="text-heading-3 text-sm">Flores Nexus Group LLC — Last updated: June 2026</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed mb-10">This page defines the exact scope of each Flores Nexus Group LLC plan. Details on this page protect both the client and Flores Nexus Group LLC by setting clear expectations before and after purchase.</p>

        <div class="space-y-0">

          <!-- Nexus Card -->
          <div class="py-8 border-t border-box-border">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <span class="bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Nexus Card</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-heading-3">$99 setup + $29/month or $299/year</span>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Includes</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-2">
                  {[
                    "Up to 5 content blocks",
                    "Up to 5 services listed",
                    "Logo + 1 main image",
                    "1 language",
                    "Contact buttons and social links",
                    "1 basic review round",
                    "Managed route: floresnexus.cards/businessname",
                    "Managed by Flores Nexus while subscription is active",
                  ].map((item) => (
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                      </svg>
                      {item}
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Does not include</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-3">
                  {[
                    "Custom domain",
                    "Contact form",
                    "Monthly updates after launch",
                    "Additional pages",
                    "Gallery or multiple images",
                    "Ownership transfer",
                    "Second language (available as add-on)",
                  ].map((item) => (
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                      </svg>
                      {item}
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Starter Website -->
          <div class="py-8 border-t border-box-border">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <span class="bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Starter Website</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-heading-3">$299 setup + $79/month or $799/year</span>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Includes</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-2">
                  {[
                    "1-page website",
                    "Up to 8 sections",
                    "Up to 10 published images",
                    "1 language",
                    "1 managed standard domain, subject to availability",
                    "Basic contact form up to 6 fields",
                    "1 review round",
                    "1 small update per month (non-accumulative)",
                    "External links for booking or payments",
                    "Hosting and technical management",
                  ].map((item) => (
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                      </svg>
                      {item}
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Does not include</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-3">
                  {[
                    "Extra pages",
                    "Accumulative updates",
                    "Automations or databases",
                    "Direct payment processing",
                    "Ownership transfer",
                    "Second language (available as add-on)",
                  ].map((item) => (
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                      </svg>
                      {item}
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Professional Website -->
          <div class="py-8 border-t border-box-border">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <span class="bg-primary text-white text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Professional Website</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-heading-3">$699 setup + $149/month or $1,499/year</span>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Includes</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-2">
                  {[
                    "Up to 5 pages",
                    "Up to 25 published images",
                    "1 language",
                    "1 managed standard domain, subject to availability",
                    "Basic contact form up to 8 fields",
                    "2 review rounds",
                    "3 small updates per month (non-accumulative)",
                    "External links for booking or payments",
                    "Hosting and technical management",
                    "Up to 2 additional standard pages available as paid add-ons",
                  ].map((item) => (
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                      </svg>
                      {item}
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-red-500 uppercase tracking-widest mb-3">Does not include</p>
                <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-3">
                  {[
                    "Pages beyond 5 (max 2 extra as add-on)",
                    "Accumulative updates",
                    "Custom apps or user accounts",
                    "API automations",
                    "Ownership transfer",
                    "Second language (available as add-on)",
                  ].map((item) => (
                    <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                      <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                      </svg>
                      {item}
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Business System -->
          <div class="py-8 border-t border-box-border">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
              <span class="bg-primary/10 text-primary text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1 rounded-full">Business System</span>
              <span class="text-xs text-heading-3">Starting at $2,500 setup + $399/month — Requires custom quote</span>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed mb-4">Scope, timeline, and inclusions are defined in a separate written proposal for each project. May include based on quote:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-sm text-heading-2">
              {[
                "User accounts",
                "Customer portal",
                "Database",
                "Custom booking",
                "Payment integration",
                "Automations",
                "API integrations",
                "Admin dashboard",
                "Document generation",
                "Custom internal workflows",
              ].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-3 mt-4 italic">Written scope required. Quote required. No direct checkout. Final pricing depends on approved scope.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Small Update Definition -->
          <div class="py-8 border-t border-box-border">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-4">Small Update Definition</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed mb-4">A small update is any change that takes less than 20 minutes and does not alter the structure of the site. This includes:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-heading-2 mb-5">
              {["Replacing one photo", "Correcting short text", "Updating phone number, hours, or address", "Updating one link or social media handle"].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-green-500 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed mb-3">This does NOT include:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-heading-3 mb-4">
              {["Adding new pages", "Redesigning sections", "Changing colors or fonts across the site", "Adding new functionality", "SEO work", "Extensive new content"].map((item) => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
                    <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4.293 4.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 8.586l4.293-4.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414L11.414 10l4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414 1.414L10 11.414l-4.293 4.293a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414L8.586 10 4.293 5.707a1 1 0 010-1.414z" clip-rule="evenodd"/>
                  </svg>
                  {item}
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-3 italic">Changes outside this definition are billed separately.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Domain Policy -->
          <div class="py-8 border-t border-box-border">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-3">Domain Policy</h2>
            <div class="text-sm text-heading-2 leading-relaxed space-y-3">
              <p>Nexus Card is published under a managed Flores Nexus route (floresnexus.cards/businessname). Custom domain is not included.</p>
              <p>Starter and Professional plans include one managed standard domain using .com, .co, or .net extensions, subject to availability. Exact domain names are not guaranteed as they may already be taken or require premium pricing.</p>
              <p>Premium domains require client approval and additional payment. Domains are administered by Flores Nexus Group LLC while the subscription is active. Transfer requires a separate process and is not included.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Add-ons -->
          <div class="py-8 border-t border-box-border">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-heading-1 mb-4">Add-Ons</h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-heading-3 mb-4">Available as separate services. Pricing may vary.</p>
            <div class="rounded-xl border border-box-border bg-box-bg overflow-hidden">
              <table class="w-full text-sm">
                <tbody>
                  {[
                    ["Maps Setup (Google + Apple initial setup)", "$50 one-time"],
                    ["Extra Small Update", "$29 one-time"],
                    ["Monthly Update Pack (3 additional updates, max 1 pack)", "$49/month"],
                    ["Second Language — Nexus Card", "$49 + $9/month or $99/year"],
                    ["Second Language — Starter", "$149 + $19/month or $199/year"],
                    ["Second Language — Professional", "$349 + $39/month or $399/year"],
                    ["Additional Standard Page (Professional only, max 2)", "$149/page"],
                    ["Third-Party Tool Connection (button/link/embed only)", "$99/tool"],
                    ["Business Email Setup (provider fees not included)", "$75 one-time"],
                    ["Domain Change", "$75 + domain cost"],
                    ["Additional Domain (redirect only)", "$35 + annual cost"],
                    ["Domain Transfer Assistance", "$75 + fees"],
                    ["Rush Delivery (with approval and capacity)", "$99 / $149 / $349"],
                    ["Website Ownership Transfer", "Quote required"],
                    ["Logo Design (not unlimited branding)", "Quote required"],
                  ].map(([item, price], i) => (
                    <tr class={`border-b border-box-border last:border-0 ${i % 2 === 0 ? "" : "bg-box-bg/50"}`}>
                      <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-heading-2">{item}</td>
                      <td class="px-4 py-2.5 text-right font-semibold text-primary whitespace-nowrap">{price}</td>
                    </tr>
                  ))}
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs text-heading-3 mt-3 italic">Maps setup does not guarantee listing approval by Google or Apple. Monthly Update Pack updates do not accumulate. Third-party tool connection includes button, link, or embed integration only — no API automation.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </main>
</Layout>
